It also involves experiments on CIFAR and ImageNet databases, which are commonly used in computer vision research. Additionally, the use of binarized convolutions in the search space suggests a focus on efficient and compressed models, which is a common concern in computer vision. 

The paper also involves optimization methods and learning strategies, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

The use of neural networks and optimization techniques also suggests a potential fit for the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the focus on architecture search and design suggests a potential fit for the computer architecture (cs.AR) sub-category.
